---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Speaking" description="Nikhil Kulkarni — speaker on AI in the enterprise, product leadership, Australia–India relations, and career transitions.">

  <div class="page-header">
    <p class="page-label">Speaking</p>
    <h1>Speaking</h1>
    <p class="intro">I speak on AI in the enterprise, product leadership, the Australia–India relationship, and career reinvention. Keynotes, panels, fireside chats, and guest lectures across Australia, India, and globally.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content">

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Topics</h2>
      <div class="topics-grid">

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>AI in the enterprise</h3>
          <p>How AI products move from capability to genuine business value. Responsible deployment, user adoption, agentic workflows, and what it takes to build AI that teams actually trust and use. Drawing on hands-on experience as founding PM lead for Rovo at Atlassian.</p>
          <p class="talk-example"><em>Representative talks:</em> "Building AI: Atlassian's approach to crafting exceptional intelligent experiences" (Team '24, Las Vegas) · "How Rovo agents are powering industry giants", panel moderator (Team '25, Barcelona) · Team on Tour AI track, Tokyo &amp; Seoul</p>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Product management &amp; technology leadership</h3>
          <p>Product strategy, scale, performance, and building high-performing teams. Practical product craft drawn from leading Jira Cloud, Rovo, and platform products at Atlassian.</p>
          <p class="talk-example"><em>Representative talks:</em> "Your product and engineering strategy should always include scale and performance" (Atlassian Team Tour 2021) · Fireside chat, SYNCS University of Sydney (2024)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Startups, innovation &amp; ecosystem building</h3>
          <p>The India–Australia innovation corridor, what it takes to go from idea to scale, and how to build conditions where entrepreneurs thrive. Speaks to founders, MBAs, and policymakers.</p>
          <p class="talk-example"><em>Representative talks:</em> TiECon Hubli 2025 keynote (400+ attendees) · New India House at SXSW Sydney, Program Director and moderator (2024) · MBA panel, Western Sydney University (2024)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Career transitions, migration &amp; diversity</h3>
          <p>Navigating career pivots, migrating to a new country, and building a path in product management from non-traditional backgrounds. Resonates with students, early-career professionals, and migrant communities.</p>
          <p class="talk-example"><em>Representative talks:</em> TiECon Hubli keynote on reinvention · Facilitator for migrant tech professionals navigating the Australian job market</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Selected engagements</h2>
      <div class="engagements-list">
        <div class="engagement">
          <span class="eng-year">2026</span>
          <div class="eng-detail"><strong>UTS AI Q&amp;A Forum:</strong> Expert Q&amp;A on AI for first-year journalism students, University of Technology Sydney</div>
        </div>
        <div class="engagement">
          <span class="eng-year">2025</span>
          <div class="eng-detail"><strong>Atlassian Team '25, Barcelona:</strong> Panel moderator, "How Rovo agents are powering industry giants"; panelists from Opella, Honeywell, Mercedes-Benz</div>
        </div>
        <div class="engagement">
          <span class="eng-year">2025</span>
          <div class="eng-detail"><strong>TiECon Hubli 2025:</strong> Keynote, "From Sainik School Bijapur to Sydney: 5 lessons on reinvention"; 400+ attendees</div>
        </div>
        <div class="engagement">
          <span class="eng-year">2025</span>
          <div class="eng-detail"><strong>Atlassian Team on Tour, Tokyo &amp; Seoul:</strong> AI track speaker on Rovo as a trusted business partner</div>
        </div>
        <div class="engagement">
          <span class="eng-year">2025</span>
          <div class="eng-detail"><strong>Atlassian Team '25, Anaheim:</strong> Panel moderator, Rovo agents; panelists from TeamViewer, HarperCollins, and Atlassian Teamwork Lab</div>
        </div>
        <div class="engagement">
          <span class="eng-year">2024</span>
          <div class="eng-detail"><strong>New India House at SXSW Sydney:</strong> Program Director and panel moderator, "Namast-AI to the Future! Why India Is Essential to Your AI Success"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="engagement">
          <span class="eng-year">2024</span>
          <div class="eng-detail"><strong>Atlassian Team '24, Las Vegas:</strong> Speaker, "Building AI: Atlassian's approach to crafting exceptional intelligent experiences"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="engagement">
          <span class="eng-year">2024</span>
          <div class="eng-detail"><strong>SYNCS Fireside Chat, University of Sydney:</strong> Product management, AI, and career progression</div>
        </div>
        <div class="engagement">
          <span class="eng-year">2024</span>
          <div class="eng-detail"><strong>Western Sydney University MBA Panel:</strong> Entrepreneurial management capabilities</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Formats</h2>
      <div class="formats">
        <span class="format-tag">Keynote</span>
        <span class="format-tag">Panel moderator</span>
        <span class="format-tag">Panelist</span>
        <span class="format-tag">Fireside chat</span>
        <span class="format-tag">Webinar host</span>
        <span class="format-tag">Guest lecturer</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section cta-section">
      <h2>Book a speaking engagement</h2>
      <p>If you're organising an event on AI, product leadership, or the Australia–India relationship and think there's a fit, I'd like to hear about it.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="cta-btn">Get in touch</a>
    </section>

  </div>

</Base>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding: 3rem 0 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .page-label {
    font-family: 'Nunito Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #c2613f;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .intro {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .content { max-width: 800px; }

  .section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
  }

  .section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  h2 {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .topics-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .topic-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
    border-top: 3px solid #c2613f;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  p {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #474747;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .talk-example {
    font-size: 0.83rem;
    color: #888;
    border-top: 1px solid #f0f0f0;
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .engagements-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .engagement {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 0.85rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0;
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .eng-year {
    font-family: 'Nunito Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #c2613f;
    min-width: 2.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .eng-detail {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #474747;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .eng-detail strong { color: #1a1a1a; }

  .formats {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .format-tag {
    font-family: 'Nunito Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #474747;
    background: #f5f5f5;
    border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .cta-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Nunito Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: #c2613f;
    color: #fff;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.4rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .cta-btn:hover { background: #a84e30; }
</style>
